HEADWORD: Cense
<hw>Cense</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[OF. <ets>cense</ets>,
F. <ets>cens</ets>, L. <ets>census</ets>. See <er>Census</er>.]</ety>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>A census; -- also, a public rate or tax.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>Howell. Bacon.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Condition; rank.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>
