<p><ent>Cense</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Cense
<hw>Cense</hw>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p. p.</pos>
<conjf>Censed</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos>
<conjf>Censing</conjf>.]</vmorph> <ety>[Abbrev. from
<ets>incense</ets>.]</ety> <def>To perfume with odors from burning gums
and spices.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The Salii sing and <qex>cense</qex> his altars round.</q>
<rj><qau>Dryden.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Cense</ent>⟦br⟧

